verbose_text: Serum CEA levels can also be increased in various nonmalignant conditions, including gastrointestinal disorders such as inflammatory bowel disease,3, 4, 5, 6 and it is reported that ulcerative colitis activity is correlated with serum CEA levels.3 However, the elevation of serum CEA levels in patients with stercoral colitis has not previously been reported in the English literature.
